description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to offer a permanent contract to an enthusiastic and patient-focused pharmacy technician, with good communication and team working skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for you to have a role in direct patient care with opportunities to develop your knowledge and clinical skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We take pride in developing our pharmacy technicians through formal and informal study, clinical supervision and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide pharmacy and medicines optimisation services to all our mental health, learning disability and neuro-rehabilitation inpatient areas, as well as to community mental health teams, crisis teams, psychiatric liaison and other specialist areas. Our Pharmacy staff are highly regarded as valued members of the multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our clinical services include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medicines reconciliation and review on admission and discharge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting patients and carers with the management of their medicines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimising medicines, taking a holistic view of both mental and physical healthcare needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in offsite community teams co-ordinating the process of medicines optimisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in clinic settings performing venepuncture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physical health and wellbeing advice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discharge planning and liaison with primary care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To find out more about working in our team, visit our page on the NHS Find Your Place website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our region offers affordable house prices and fantastic quality of life opportunities. It includes some of Britain’s most beautiful scenery and coastline, national parks and ancient heritage sites. Transport links with other UK regions are excellent. To find out more about our beautiful region, please visit north east england.com&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must be registered with the General Pharmaceutical Council. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We offer &lt;/strong&gt;flexible working opportunities and would consider part time applicants for this position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lorraine Woodhouse, Specialist Pharmacy Technician on telephone number 0191 566 7350 or mobile number 07814 603 641 or email: lorraine.woodhouse@cntw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
